spectra.observer: M. R. Siebert, E. Strasburger, C. Rojas-Bravo, R. J. Foley
spectra.remarks: The spectrum is very blue, peaking blueward of 3200 A in the rest frame.  Superposed on the continuum are several emission features, including He II 4686 and Balmer lines.  We measure a He II 4686 FWHM of 17,700 km/s, and a H-alpha FWHM of 13,200 km/s.  Assuming AT2019qiz is at a distance of 65 Mpc, it currently has an absolute g-band magnitude of Mg ~ -17.5 mag.  The ZTF light curve indicates that the TDE is young and still increasing in brightness.
